rComments: Although Prof. Lan is very nice and easy-going, it's hard to look over the language barrier. He knows that and is trying very hard to improve his English, which is great. Quizzes every week, they are usually identical to last year's quizzes with some changes. They come right from the textbook. Midterm and final were super easy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Light workload, high grade, but still need effort especially before the final exam. Professor Lan is knowledgable and thoughtful, but his voice is really hypnotic.
The class gave him a good around of applause at the end of the last lecture.

Pretty good in all. Tests are simple and open book. Textbook is not necessary, the PPT and note are enough for exams. The lecture is really boring, and the prof has accent. But the final grade is good.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'So many papers', 'Group projects']

rComments: If you can make it through a class and actually understand what he says, you have a gift. He seems like he would be an amazing professor, and he seems to be a nice guy during office hours, but classes are basically pointless. The midterm was fair and the final was fair, but very hard. The quizzes come straight from the textbook.
His accent is unfortunately very intrusive, and hard to understand what he says. Though he is very kind.

Kind prof,but there lies a big language barrier.Quizzes had a lot of problems needing iterative solutions (PITA).Middy needed double interpolation (easy if you applied the equations outlined in the appendix of the tbook).Final was fair and non-cumulative (5 questions:Residual gas,diesel cycle,steam cycle,vapor-comp+heatXchanger).Treat book as bible
He is a great prof!!! He is super knowledgeable and very willing to help others.
Honestly going to class is so useless because your're not going to learn anything. The language barrier is too damn high! Midterms are usually hard but the final he makes it easy.
Professor Lan loves teaching and does his best to make sure everyone understands the concepts. Really connects and relates well to students. The course overall is fair and not very difficult.

Very knowledgeable professor. He is able to answer any questions you throw at him. The only thing is the language barrier. Many people had trouble understanding his English and thus didn't attend his classes.
Great guy. One of the best in the department.
Boring...no point of going ot class. Just read the book.
He's a very nice prof. even though sometimes it's impossible to understand his accent. However, he takes his time answering students' questions during or outside office hours.

He's a nice prof. He gets nervous easily when students ask him questions in class. Midterm and Final was pretty fair. Very eager to help us and asnwer out questions. Very caring and make sures we're all doing well.
